snippet: Prime Minister Shinzo Abe said he was “completely on the same page” with President Trump on North Korea and trade, but the president made it clear that being in lock step with him is a precarious position.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Standing at side-by-side lecterns inside the gilded Akasaka State Guest House in Tokyo, President Trump and Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan sought to show the world the strength of what Mr. Abe called their “unshakable bond.”
abstract: Prime Minister Shinzo Abe said he was “completely on the same page” with President Trump on North Korea and trade, but the president made it clear that being in lock step with him is a precarious position.

snippet: The competitive lanes are set as candidates vie for black voters, women, younger voters — but they are fluid. One thing seems sure: Joseph R. Biden’s lead will be tested.
lead_paragraph: NEWTON, Iowa — Joseph R. Biden Jr. has built an early lead in the month since he entered the presidential campaign, confidently projecting himself as the Democratic front-runner and the candidate best positioned to defeat President Trump.
abstract: The competitive lanes are set as candidates vie for black voters, women, younger voters — but they are fluid. One thing seems sure: Joseph R. Biden’s lead will be tested.

snippet: The White House press secretary also defended the president’s approach to North Korea and the review of the Russia investigation’s roots.
lead_paragraph: President Trump and the North Korean leader, Kim Jong-un, “agree” in their negative assessment of former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., the White House press secretary, Sarah Huckabee Sanders, said on Sunday.
abstract: The White House press secretary also defended the president’s approach to North Korea and the review of the Russia investigation’s roots.

snippet: Acknowledging the boom, and then a quick pivot to other issues or a nuanced argument on what personal economic well-being means.
lead_paragraph: NASHUA, N.H. — Ask Democratic candidates for president how they would challenge President Trump’s boasts about the economy, and the initial response tends to be less an attack than a concession.
abstract: Acknowledging the boom, and then a quick pivot to other issues or a nuanced argument on what personal economic well-being means.

snippet: President Trump played down North Korea’s recent tests of short-range ballistic missiles, undercutting declarations by both Prime Minister Shinzo Abe and the president’s own national security adviser.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — President Trump kicked off the first full day of a state visit to Japan on Sunday by playing down North Korea’s recent tests of short-range ballistic missiles, undercutting declarations by both Prime Minister Shinzo Abe and the president’s own national security adviser that the launches violated United Nations resolutions.

snippet: The 2020 candidates who seek to oust Trump must defend liberal democracy against illiberalism at home and abroad.
lead_paragraph: Every political campaign involves a choice between elevating political discourse and degrading it. The 2016 election brought a pornographic film star into prime time and made “pussy” front-page news. How it could get any worse in 2020 is difficult to imagine. But the problem isn’t the word “pussy” and the pornification of politics, however demeaning; the problem is the word “nationalism” and the abandonment of liberalism.

snippet: We called up the experts to help answer an age-old question: What’s the best type of book to bring to the shore?
lead_paragraph: Sunscreen, water bottle, umbrella: check. You can’t forget a book — but how to choose? We spoke to booksellers in popular vacation destinations across the country about how they define the perfect “beach read,” their predictions for this year’s best sellers and more. Their answers have been edited and condensed.
